2. PHYSICS BACKGROUND & CONSTRAINTS

2.1 Orbital Environment

LEO Radiation Environment:

· Altitude: 400-500 km
· Radiation types:
  1. Trapped protons (South Atlantic Anomaly): 10⁴-10⁶/cm²/s
  2. Galactic cosmic rays: 4-5 particles/cm²/s
  3. Solar particle events: 10-100× increase during flares

Radiation Effects:

1. Total Ionizing Dose (TID): 100-300 rad/year
2. Single Event Effects (SEE):
   · Single Event Upset (SEU): 10⁻⁵-10⁻³ errors/bit/day
   · Multiple Bit Upset (MBU): 10-30% of SEUs in dense memory
3. Displacement Damage: Minimal for photonics

Thermal Environment:

· Temperature range: -40°C to +85°C (233-358 K)
· Orbit period: 90 minutes (55 min sun, 35 min eclipse)
· Heat dissipation: Radiation only (no convection)

2.2 Quantum Limits

Landauer Bound:
Minimum energy per irreversible operation:
$E_{\min} = kT \ln 2$

· At 300 K: $E_{\min} = 2.8 \times 10^{-21}$ J/bit
· At 15 mK: $E_{\min} = 1.4 \times 10^{-25}$ J/bit

Photonic Energy Efficiency:

· Photon energy at 1550 nm: $E_{\text{photon}} = \frac{hc}{\lambda} = 1.28 \times 10^{-19}$ J
· Theoretical limit: 1 photon per bit operation
· Practical limit: 10-100 photons per operation

Noise Limits:

· Shot noise: $\sigma_{\text{shot}} = \sqrt{N_{\text{photons}}}$
· Thermal noise: $\sigma_{\text{thermal}} = \sqrt{4kTRB}$
· Quantum limit: SNR ∝ $N_{\text{photons}}$

2.3 Material Properties

Si₃N₄ Photonics:

· Refractive index: $n = 2.0$ @ 1550 nm
· Propagation loss: < 0.1 dB/cm
· Thermal coefficient: 0.1 pm/K
· Radiation tolerance: > 1 Mrad (Si)

Superconducting Qubits (Optional):

· Niobium nitride (NbN)
· Critical temperature: $T_c = 16$ K
· Coherence time: $T_1 ≈ 20$ μs, $T_2 ≈ 15$ μs (orbital)
· Readout fidelity: > 99%

