3. ARCHITECTURAL DESIGN

3.1 System Overview

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                      ORBITAL HD-AGI ARCHITECTURE                    │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  Layer 1: Photonic Frontend (15W)                                   │
│    • Si₃N₄ Microcomb Laser: 64 wavelengths @ 1550 nm               │
│    • AWGR: 64×24 = 1536 channels with 8-bit interleaving           │
│    • Modulators: Mach-Zehnder, 10 GHz bandwidth                    │
│    • Photodetectors: APD arrays, 85% quantum efficiency            │
│    • Operations: HD binding (XOR), bundling (majority)             │
│                                                                     │
│  Layer 2: Electronic Backend (20W)                                  │
│    • FPGA: Xilinx Virtex-5QV or equivalent radiation-hardened      │
│    • Memory: 2GB ECC DDR4, 10 GB/s bandwidth                       │
│    • Storage: 64GB NVMe SSD with wear leveling                     │
│    • Processing: Bayesian verification, adaptive control           │
│                                                                     │
│  Layer 3: Control System (5W)                                       │
│    • Radiation monitors: particle detectors                        │
│    • Thermal management: Peltier coolers, heat pipes               │
│    • Power management: MPPT solar controllers                      │
│    • Communication: S-band transceiver, 1 Gbps                     │
│                                                                     │
│  Layer 4: Power System (5W overhead)                                │
│    • Solar panels: 60W peak, GaAs triple-junction                  │
│    • Batteries: 100 Wh Li-ion, 1000+ cycle life                    │
│    • Regulation: 85% efficiency DC-DC converters                   │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

3.2 Data Flow

```
Satellite Sensors
    ↓
[Photonic Encoding] → 1536D sparse binary vectors
    ↓
[AWGR Interleaving] → Burst-resistant mapping
    ↓
[HD Operations] → Binding/Bundling via photonic interference
    ↓
[Electronic Verification] → Bayesian confidence scoring
    ↓
[Adaptive Control] → Dimension switching, refresh scheduling
    ↓
[Memory Storage] → Compressed sparse format
    ↓
Ground Station / Onboard Decision
```

3.3 Key Architectural Innovations

1. Photonic HD Computing:

· Binding: Implemented via optical interference (XOR)
  $I_{\text{out}} = |E_1 + E_2|^2 \propto \text{XOR}(\phi_1, \phi_2)$
· Bundling: Majority vote via coherent addition
  $E_{\text{sum}} = \sum_{i=1}^n E_i$, threshold detection
· Energy efficiency: 100 fJ/operation vs 10 pJ electronic

2. AWGR Interleaving:

· 1536 channels = 64 wavelengths × 24 ports
· 8-bit interleaving with 2 guard channels per block
· Burst resistance: reduces MBU probability by 40-60%

3. Adaptive Dimension Switching:

· Normal mode: 1536D (baseline LEO)
· High radiation: 1024D (SAA passage)
· Extreme radiation: 768D (solar flare)
· Safe mode: 512D (emergency)

4. Hybrid Memory Hierarchy:

· Photonic cache: 128 KB volatile (working set)
· Electronic storage: 2GB non-volatile (long-term)
· Refresh strategy: Orbit-aware predictive refresh

