4.1 Photonic Components

Si₃N₄ Microcomb Laser:

· Wavelengths: 64 channels
· Spacing: 100 GHz (0.8 nm)
· Power: 20 mW total optical power
· Linewidth: < 100 kHz
· Stability: < 1 pm/K thermal drift

Arrayed Waveguide Grating Router (AWGR):

· Ports: 24 input × 24 output
· Free spectral range: 6.4 THz
· Insertion loss: < 2.8 dB
· Crosstalk: < -26 dB
· Uniformity: < 1.5 dB
· Chip size: 8 × 8 mm²

Modulators & Detectors:

· Modulators: Mach-Zehnder, 10 GHz, Vπ = 2V
· Photodetectors: Avalanche photodiodes (APD)
· Quantum efficiency: > 85%
· Dark current: < 1 nA
· Bandwidth: 10 GHz

4.2 Electronic Components

Radiation-Hardened FPGA:

· Device: Xilinx Virtex-5QV or equivalent
· Logic cells: 65,536
· Block RAM: 2,304 KB
· DSP slices: 192
· SEU immunity: Latch-based, TID > 1 Mrad
· Power: 15W typical, 25W peak

Memory System:

· Main memory: 2GB DDR4 with ECC
· Bandwidth: 10 GB/s
· Storage: 64GB NVMe SSD
· Cache: 256 KB SRAM (on-FPGA)

Sensors & Interfaces:

· Radiation sensor: PIN diode array
· Temperature: 8-channel PT1000
· GPS: Space-grade with < 10m accuracy
· Communication: S-band, 1 Gbps

4.3 Mechanical & Thermal

Physical Dimensions:

· Total mass: 15 kg
· Volume: 20 × 20 × 30 cm
· Structure: Aluminum 6061 with tantalum shielding

Thermal Management:

· Cold plate: 15 mK (quantum section)
· Main electronics: 0°C to 40°C
· Radiators: 200 cm² surface area
· Heat pipes: 50W capacity

Radiation Shielding:

· Tantalum: 5 mm thickness
· Total dose tolerance: 100 krad
· SEU rate reduction: 10×
· Mass penalty: 3 kg

