7.2 Energy Harvesting

Solar Power:

· Orbit: 400 km altitude, 51.6° inclination
· Sun period: 55 minutes per orbit
· Eclipse period: 35 minutes per orbit
· Average power: $P_{\text{avg}} = P_{\text{peak}} \cdot \frac{t_{\text{sun}}}{t_{\text{orbit}}} \cdot \eta$
  · $P_{\text{peak}} = 60$ W
  · $\eta = 0.85$ (system efficiency)
  · $P_{\text{avg}} = 60 \cdot \frac{55}{90} \cdot 0.85 = 31.2$ W

Battery System:

· Type: Li-ion, 100 Wh capacity
· Depth of discharge: 30% for longevity
· Usable energy: 30 Wh
· Eclipse support: $\frac{30 \text{ Wh}}{45 \text{ W}} = 0.67$ hours (40 minutes)
· Margin: 5 minutes excess capacity

Power Management IC:

· MPPT efficiency: > 98%
· DC-DC conversion: 92% efficiency
· Load switching: < 100 μs transition
· Fault protection: Over-current, over-voltage, reverse polarity

7.3 Low-Power Modes

Mode Power Consumption:

1. Active Learning: 45W (full capability)
2. Inference Only: 30W (photonic reduced, electronics active)
3. Standby: 15W (minimum sensors, memory retention)
4. Safe Mode: 5W (critical functions only)
5. Hibernation: 1W (wake-on-event)

Duty Cycling:

· Learning: 10% duty cycle (5.4 minutes/hour)
· Inference: 40% duty cycle (24 minutes/hour)
· Standby: 50% duty cycle (30 minutes/hour)
· Average power: 22.5W (within solar generation capacity)

