APPENDICES

A. Mathematical Derivations

HD Capacity Derivation:
For $D$-dimensional vectors with sparsity $s$, the number of distinguishable vectors is given by the birthday paradox limit:
$N_{\max} \approx \sqrt{\frac{\pi}{2} \cdot \binom{D}{sD}}$
For $D=1536$, $s=0.08$: $N_{\max} \approx 1.2 \times 10^6$

Radiation Error Analysis:
Probability of $k$ errors in $n$ bits:
$P(k) = \binom{n}{k} p^k (1-p)^{n-k}$
where $p = BER \cdot \text{exposure time}$
For $n = 1536 \cdot 0.08 = 123$, $p = 10^{-4}$:
$P(\text{no error}) = (1-p)^n = 0.988$

Energy Efficiency Calculation:
Photonic binding: $E_{\text{bind}} = N_{\text{photons}} \cdot E_{\text{photon}}$
With $N_{\text{photons}} = 100$, $E_{\text{photon}} = 1.28 \times 10^{-19}$ J:
$E_{\text{bind}} = 1.28 \times 10^{-17}$ J = 12.8 fJ
System overhead: 8× → $E_{\text{total}} = 100$ fJ

B. Component Specifications

Detailed Parts List:

1. Si₃N₄ microcomb laser: Wavelength: 1550±25 nm, Power: 20 mW
2. AWGR chip: Size: 8×8 mm, Channels: 1536, Loss: <2.8 dB
3. FPGA: Xilinx Virtex-5QV, Logic: 65k cells, Power: 15W
4. Memory: 2GB DDR4-2400, ECC enabled
5. Solar panels: GaAs triple-junction, 60W peak
6. Batteries: Li-ion, 100 Wh, 28V nominal

Interfaces:

· Photonic: FC/APC connectors, single mode
· Electronic: SpaceWire, LVDS, I2C, SPI
· Power: 28V primary bus, 12V/5V/3.3V secondary
· Thermal: Heat pipes, cold plates, radiators

